  number={},
  pages={1-8},
  abstract={Gastrointestinal (GI) cancer involves the digestive tract and is not easy to detect because it comes with vague signs and intricate medical reports. The present study puts forward a new use of RoBERTa large, a transformer language model, and Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG). Our model exhibits important advancements with three innovations: Domain-specific embeddings employing medically fine-tuned RoBERTa (Robustly Optimized BERT Pretraining Approach), dynamic knowledge incorporation of latest research through RAG (Retrieval-Augmented Generation) architecture, and hybrid ranking leveraging semantic and keyword-based relevance. Experimental results establish 51% cosine similarity in test set responses with retaining clinical coherence.},
  keywords={Technological innovation;Databases;Retrieval augmented generation;Semantics;Chatbots;Transformers;Gastrointestinal tract;Vectors;Medical diagnostic imaging;Cancer;RoBERTa;Gastrointestinal Cancer;Retrieval-Augmented Generation;Biomedical NLP;Vector Database},
